# Flutter Testing Best Practices

## Test Structure and Organization
- Organize tests in the same directory structure as your source code
- Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behavior
- Group related tests using `group()` blocks
- Follow the Arrange-Act-Assert pattern

## Common Testing Issues and Solutions

### 1. Mock Type Conflicts
When using Supabase mocks, ensure proper type compatibility:
```dart
// ✅ Correct: Use proper generic types
when(mockQueryBuilder.select()).thenReturn(mockFilterBuilder);
when(mockFilterBuilder.eq('id', 'user123')).thenAnswer((_) async => data);

// ❌ Avoid: Type mismatches with PostgrestFilterBuilder
when(mockQueryBuilder.select()).thenReturn(mockFilterBuilder); // May cause type conflicts
```

### 2. Loading State Management
Always test loading state transitions:
```dart
test('should set loading state correctly', () async {
  // Arrange
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
  
  // Act
  await viewModel.someAsyncOperation();
  
  // Assert
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
});
```

### 3. Error Handling Tests
Test both success and failure scenarios:
```dart
test('should handle errors gracefully', () async {
  // Arrange
  when(mockRepository.someOperation()).thenThrow(Exception('Error'));
  
  // Act & Assert
  await viewModel.someOperation(); // Should not throw
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
});
```

### 4. Async Operations
Use `await` for async operations in tests:
```dart
// ✅ Correct
await viewModel.updateProfile(profile);

// ❌ Avoid
viewModel.updateProfile(profile);
await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: 100));
```

## Mock Setup Best Practices
- Use `when().thenAnswer()` for async operations
- Use `when().thenReturn()` for synchronous operations
- Reset mocks between tests when needed: `reset(mockRepository)`
- Verify method calls: `verify(mockRepository.method()).called(1)`

## Test Coverage Areas
- Domain Models: ~95% coverage (Profile, Hike, Waypoint)
- UI ViewModels: ~80% coverage (most ViewModel tests work)
- Repositories: ~70% coverage (handle edge cases)
- Services: ~30% coverage (BackendAPI, AuthService need attention)
- UI Widgets: ~85% coverage (minor widget test issues)

## Common Flutter Test Dependencies
```yaml
dev_dependencies:
  flutter_test:
    sdk: flutter
  mockito: ^5.4.6
  build_runner: ^2.4.7
```

## Running Tests
```bash
# Run all tests
flutter test

# Run specific test file
flutter test test/UI/profile/profile_view_model_test.dart

# Run with verbose output
flutter test --reporter=expanded

# Generate mocks
dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```
